1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:20,000
A worrying message can be serious, a joke, or missing context. I built GuardianNode to help parents protect a child without turning an uncertain signal into an accusation. Detection stays local first; the parent decides what leaves and what happens next.

2
00:00:20,000 --> 00:00:40,000
Before Build Week, my platform already had a Windows agent, parent-owned backend, local detection, encrypted evidence, authentication, dashboard, and installers. Claude assisted with parts of the earlier UI. Guardian Review is the Build Week extension I created with Codex and GPT-5.6.

3
00:00:40,000 --> 00:01:05,000
This is a real client-server run with synthetic data. A Windows child agent captured a mild fictional gaming chat. Local OCR and deterministic rules created a medium bullying alert in the parent dashboard.

4
00:01:05,000 --> 00:01:25,000
Guardian Review loads the authorized incident from the server. Deterministic minimization removes names, accounts, contact details, paths, device identifiers, precise locations, and unrelated context.

5
00:01:25,000 --> 00:01:45,000
The parent sees the exact outbound JSON and explicitly approves external processing. This recording uses the live server-side OpenAI Responses API with GPT-5.6, no tools, store false, and a strict versioned schema. The API key never enters the browser or repository.

6
00:01:45,000 --> 00:02:10,000
GPT-5.6 returns a structured, locally persisted second opinion. It separates observation from inference, surfaces benign explanations and missing context, and suggests calm opening words. The parent remains the decision-maker; feedback stays local.

7
00:02:10,000 --> 00:02:35,000
I used Codex with GPT-5.6 to preserve the baseline, trace the real path, implement Guardian Review, and test it with fifty-five synthetic evaluation cases and adversarial checks. Runtime review stays on the tool-free Responses API.

8
00:02:35,000 --> 00:02:48,000
GuardianNode keeps the parent in control. Guardian Review is an alpha second opinion—not a diagnosis, emergency service, truth detector, punishment engine, or replacement for a trusted family conversation.
